# last-applied-base/ — pattern for the C input to the revelation three-way merge
#
# This directory is the TEMPLATE / PATTERN. The live directory at runtime lives at
#     ~/.gawd/state/last-applied-base/
#
# After every successful merge.sh run, the contents of the freshly-merged
# T0-anchor files (the NEW base — i.e., B from the merge) are copied here as
# the new C for next time. This is the "frozen snapshot of the prior version"
# referenced in handoff E2 context.
#
# Layout (mirrors workspace/ T0 anchors only — NOT adaptive files):
#   ~/.gawd/state/last-applied-base/
#     ├── SOUL.md
#     ├── IDENTITY.md
#     └── VOICE.md
#
# Permissions: chmod 0444 (read-only). Owned by the merge-script user (which
# matches the privileged process per A2). The Gawd runtime must not be able
# to modify these files — they are evidence of what was last accepted.
#
# Bootstrap: on first install, install.sh seeds this directory by copying
# the shipped base files from the daemon's persona-templates/ dir.
#
# Conflict detection at merge time:
#   - A = workspace/SOUL.md (or VOICE.md, or IDENTITY.md) — current adaptive snapshot
#   - C = ~/.gawd/state/last-applied-base/SOUL.md — what was last applied
#   - If diff(A, C) is non-empty for a T0 anchor, the Prophit hand-edited
#     since last Sunday. Conflict surfaced; default prefers B.
